Grammar

    0 $accept: SD $end

    1 SD: S

    2 S: IF CMP THEN STMT

    3 CMP: ID ROP ID

    4 STMT: ID AOP ID


Terminals, with rules where they appear

    $end (0) 0
    error (256)
    IF (258) 2
    THEN (259) 2
    ID (260) 3 4
    ROP (261) 3
    AOP (262) 4


Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

    $accept (8)
        on left: 0
    SD (9)
        on left: 1
        on right: 0
    S (10)
        on left: 2
        on right: 1
    CMP (11)
        on left: 3
        on right: 2
    STMT (12)
        on left: 4
        on right: 2


State 0

    0 $accept: • SD $end

    IF  shift, and go to state 1

    SD  go to state 2
    S   go to state 3


State 1

    2 S: IF • CMP THEN STMT

    ID  shift, and go to state 4

    CMP  go to state 5


State 2

    0 $accept: SD • $end

    $end  shift, and go to state 6


State 3

    1 SD: S •

    $default  reduce using rule 1 (SD)


State 4

    3 CMP: ID • ROP ID

    ROP  shift, and go to state 7


State 5

    2 S: IF CMP • THEN STMT

    THEN  shift, and go to state 8


State 6

    0 $accept: SD $end •

    $default  accept


State 7

    3 CMP: ID ROP • ID

    ID  shift, and go to state 9


State 8

    2 S: IF CMP THEN • STMT

    ID  shift, and go to state 10

    STMT  go to state 11


State 9

    3 CMP: ID ROP ID •

    $default  reduce using rule 3 (CMP)


State 10

    4 STMT: ID • AOP ID

    AOP  shift, and go to state 12


State 11

    2 S: IF CMP THEN STMT •

    $default  reduce using rule 2 (S)


State 12

    4 STMT: ID AOP • ID

    ID  shift, and go to state 13


State 13

    4 STMT: ID AOP ID •

    $default  reduce using rule 4 (STMT)
